To stream output from a LangGraph graph deployed on an Agent Server, you can use the LangGraph SDKs (Python or JavaScript) or the HTTP API [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /]. 

Here are the primary ways to stream output:

### 1. Using the Python SDK
You can use `client.runs.stream` and iterate over the stream using an `async for` loop. Specify your desired stream mode (e.g., `"updates"` or `"values"`) using the `stream_mode` parameter [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /]:

```python
from langgraph_sdk import get_client

client = get_client(url="<DEPLOYMENT_URL>", api_key="<API_KEY>")

async for event in client.runs.stream(
    thread_id,
    "agent",
    input={
        "messages": [
            {"role": "user", "content": "Your input here"}
        ]
    },
    stream_mode="updates",
):
    if event.event == "updates":
        print(event.data)
```
*(Source: [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /])*

### 2. Using the JavaScript SDK
You can similarly use `client.runs.stream` with an asynchronous generator [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /]:

```javascript
import { Client } from "@langchain/langgraph-sdk";

const client = new Client({ apiUrl: "<DEPLOYMENT_URL>", apiKey: "<API_KEY>" });

const streamResponse = client.runs.stream(threadId, "agent", {
  input: {
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Your input here" }],
  },
  streamMode: "updates",
});

for await (const event of streamResponse) {
  if (event.event === "updates") {
    console.log(event.data);
  }
}
```
*(Source: [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /])*

### 3. Using the cURL / HTTP API
You can send a `POST` request to the streaming run endpoint [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /]:

```bash
curl --request POST \
  --url "<DEPLOYMENT_URL>/threads/<THREAD_ID>/runs/stream" \
  --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --header "x-api-key: <API_KEY>" \
  --data '{
    "assistant_id": "agent",
    "input": {
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Your input here"
        }
      ]
    },
    "stream_mode": "updates"
  }'
```
*(Source: [How to collect user feedback for Agent Server runs › /])*

### 4. Event Streaming V2 APIs (Alternative)
If you have V2 event streaming enabled (`FF_V2_EVENT_STREAMING`), you can also use these dedicated endpoints for real-time stream events [Agent Server changelog › /v0.11/Changes/]:
* `POST /threads/{thread_id}/stream/events`
* `WS /threads/{thread_id}/stream/events` (WebSockets)
